// STOCHASTIC MOMENTUM INDEX (SMI) - Extreme Tutorial Mode</span></div><div class=\"code-line\" style=\"white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"display:inline-block; width:2em; text-align:right; margin-right:1em; color:#9ca3af; user-select:none;\">3</span><span class=\"c1\">// =============================================================================</span></div><div class=\"code-line\" style=\"white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"display:inline-block; width:2em; text-align:right; margin-right:1em; color:#9ca3af; user-select:none;\">4</span><span class=\"c1\">//</span></div><div class=\"code-line\" style=\"white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"display:inline-block; width:2em; text-align:right; margin-right:1em; color:#9ca3af; user-select:none;\">5</span><span class=\"c1\">// [What] Stochastic Momentum Index (SMI), developed by William Blau, is an</span></div><div class=\"code-line\" style=\"white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"display:inline-block; width:2em; text-align:right; margin-right:1em; color:#9ca3af; user-select:none;\">6</span><span class=\"c1\">//        enhanced version of the traditional Stochastic oscillator. It measures</span></div><div class=\"code-line\" style=\"white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"display:inline-block; width:2em; text-align:right; margin-right:1em; color:#9ca3af; user-select:none;\">7</span><span class=\"c1\">//        the distance from the midpoint of the high-low range, not just the</span></div><div class=\"code-line\" style=\"white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"display:inline-block; width:2em; text-align:right; margin-right:1em; color:#9ca3af; user-select:none;\">8</span><span class=\"c1\">//        position within the range, outputting -100 to +100.</span></div><div class=\"code-line\" style=\"white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"display:inline-block; width:2em; text-align:right; margin-right:1em; color:#9ca3af; user-select:none;\">9</span><span class=\"c1\">//</span></div><div class=\"code-line\" style=\"white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"display:i